From ad723cb32d3fc65e6b2338310a76ac12930628c4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 15:13:09 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 07/17] task4: grouping, ranking and index rendering in
 publication.py

group_notes merges duplicates transitively: same resolved attempt hash,
or tag-set Jaccard >= 0.5 (both non-empty). Representative = best
verdict then most recent. rank_groups serves four tiers (verified/high,
unverifiable, honest-refuted, failed), recency within tier.
render_index generates a deterministic index.md with a status column
and see-also sublines; links are POSIX paths relative to base_dir;
missing member files degrade instead of crashing.

Reviewed; two blocking issues (absolute links, missing-file crash)
found and fixed. 668 passed, ruff clean.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
